# Beacon Conventions

- Use TypeScript everywhere; never use the `any` type.
- Every API response is JSON shaped as `{ data: ... }` on success or `{ error: ... }` on failure.
- Shared types live in `packages/shared` and are imported, never copy-pasted.
- Every new feature gets a matching test.
- Keep functions short and add a short comment to each.
- Always use pnpm in this project, never npm or yarn.
